Tick-borne encephalitis virus nonstructural protein NS5 induces RANTES expression dependent on the RNA-dependent RNA polymerase activity. J Immunol 2018; 201: 53– 68. 29760190

note.p: This work provides a demonstration that CCL5/RANTES expression in the CNS is induced via IRF-3 signaling pathway, which causes neuroinflammation and migration of T lymphocytes and blood monocytes
